case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Partial remains with soft tissues
case_circumstances: The incomplete skeletal remains were recovered from McCoy's Creek in Jacksonville on 12/8/2014.  The time of death was estimated to have been several months to several years.  A male, Nike tennis shoe, size 10.5, and a sock was recovered as well.  The body is believed to be a white male, likely in his 40's, 50's, or 60's at the time of his death.  He was likely 5'3" to 5'9" tall.  He had osteoarthritis and peridontal disease.
